35:20.000 --> 35:21.960
Green slime and
some sulfuric water.

35:22.240 --> 35:24.120
- Ah.
- So what happens now?

35:24.280 --> 35:27.320
Well, now we take these and run them
through some very powerful,

35:27.440 --> 35:30.040
very expensive equipment
in a lab in Toronto.

35:30.560 --> 35:31.640
Gotcha.

35:32.560 --> 35:34.120
So what're you shooting?

35:34.640 --> 35:36.760
Me? Nothing.

35:37.240 --> 35:38.440
Where did you get the needle?

35:38.600 --> 35:40.840
See, I knew you were going
to front on me for that.

35:40.920 --> 35:42.720
- You gotta stop.
- I already have.

35:42.960 --> 35:44.760
Owen, what are you doing down here, man?

35:44.880 --> 35:47.520
Well, seeing as how I live here,
I guess it's home.

35:48.080 --> 35:51.720
You don't have any other place
you could go, like back home... home?

35:52.920 --> 35:54.520
North Platte, Nebraska?

35:55.040 --> 35:57.120
My dad drives a truck,
he's never home.

35:57.240 --> 36:00.600
And my mom's...
She's found the Lord... And so

36:00.760 --> 36:03.240
it's just better not being around.

36:04.640 --> 36:06.080
Does she know you're here?

36:06.200 --> 36:07.760
- She doesn't care.
- How do you know?

36:09.120 --> 36:12.480
Because every time I go to the bus station,

36:12.640 --> 36:15.680
I see the posters of
all the missing kids and runaways

36:15.800 --> 36:19.080
of parents who want to find them.
I look and I don't see me.

36:20.600 --> 36:24.000
See. She probably doesn't
even know I'm gone.

36:26.320 --> 36:28.560
So this is home... my home.

36:31.440 --> 36:32.920
You got a cell?

36:33.960 --> 36:35.440
Come on.

36:43.240 --> 36:44.400
That's my number.

36:44.640 --> 36:46.920
Call me in a week,
I'll let you know what we find.

36:47.600 --> 36:48.440
Or...

36:48.840 --> 36:50.600
You know...
if you need anything.

36:51.760 --> 36:53.520
But not collect!

36:54.040 --> 36:55.640
- Bye Owen.
- Bye.

37:07.200 --> 37:09.200
His EEG was almost flat?

37:09.360 --> 37:10.920
Oh, my God...

37:12.120 --> 37:14.440
Why wasn't I told, Doctor?

37:16.960 --> 37:17.920
Right.

37:18.960 --> 37:21.960
No. He's... he's doing fine.

37:22.440 --> 37:25.320
It sounds like the same trouble
he's had in the past. So...

37:25.680 --> 37:27.080
Yes. I will.

37:27.760 --> 37:29.240
Yes. Thank you.

37:32.680 --> 37:34.720
Hey. It's me. Uh...

37:35.520 --> 37:37.080
I'm, uh...

37:37.600 --> 37:39.720
Just... uh...
Call me when you can.

37:39.960 --> 37:41.000
Okay?

37:41.800 --> 37:42.720
Bye.

37:59.480 --> 38:00.520
Ah.

38:01.360 --> 38:02.720
You think he'll be okay?

38:02.960 --> 38:04.160
I don't know.

38:04.400 --> 38:07.640
Well... Where should I start
with this stuff?

38:08.120 --> 38:09.760
Have Carlos do the blood.

38:09.880 --> 38:11.640
Check everything
with Sunshine's file.

38:11.720 --> 38:13.880
Get Mayko on a computer
run for symptoms.

38:14.080 --> 38:18.040
See if she can find anything
even remotely close, and...

38:18.320 --> 38:20.400
You know the rest of the drill.

38:20.520 --> 38:21.560
Sure.

38:21.840 --> 38:22.960
Taxi!

38:28.560 --> 38:29.960
Nice.
- Thank you.

38:30.200 --> 38:31.440
- We'll talk.
- Okay.

38:31.480 --> 38:32.920
Talk. Fuck! Bob!

38:33.120 --> 38:34.960
What? Oh. Am I coming?

38:35.120 --> 38:35.920
Yes!

38:39.360 --> 38:41.120
Bob Melnikov.

39:01.760 --> 39:03.480
Good afte...

39:04.200 --> 39:05.680
Good afternoon.

39:06.040 --> 39:07.520
Thank you all for coming.

39:09.280 --> 39:11.040
I promise you an interesting talk

39:11.200 --> 39:13.320
even though it might be full of hot air.

39:17.960 --> 39:20.000
Well. So much for starting
off with a joke.

39:22.920 --> 39:26.040
60% of the world's
population lives in Asia.

39:32.440 --> 39:35.040
- Okay, so... Hang on a second.
- What are you doing?

39:35.240 --> 39:37.480
What? For the... No. Never mind.
Okay, we'll be back tonight.

39:37.600 --> 39:39.040
- Okay. Okay.
- Thanks, Jill.

39:42.600 --> 39:43.960
Over the past three decades

39:44.080 --> 39:46.720
large-scale economic developments
have transformed Asia,

39:46.880 --> 39:49.920
not only on the ground,
but in the skies as well.

40:01.440 --> 40:04.520
A large, brownish haze now covers
much of this part of the world,

40:04.760 --> 40:06.200
posing a threat not only to Asia

40:06.360 --> 40:08.760
and her people,
but to the entire planet.

40:09.160 --> 40:12.080
Thank you and
enjoy the rest of the conference.

40:25.680 --> 40:27.840
He works at my lab, you know.

40:29.640 --> 40:31.920
Bob, we are gonna send
you out on the road.

40:32.480 --> 40:33.760
Come on, David.

40:33.920 --> 40:35.480
Serious, you're gonna be a big star.

40:35.640 --> 40:37.640
- Heather, am I right?
- I can't deny it.

40:38.200 --> 40:39.800
Who needs another drink?

40:40.040 --> 40:42.080
Gentlemen, I would love to,
but I have dinner plans.

40:42.120 --> 40:43.560
- Ah!
- And a show.

40:43.640 --> 40:46.640
A show? What better show could
you possibly get than this one right here?

40:47.960 --> 40:49.440
It's tempting...

40:52.200 --> 40:54.080
- So, Heather...
- Yeah?

40:54.280 --> 40:56.240
When do you think
you'll be able to come and visit?

40:56.360 --> 40:57.880
- Well, just as soon as--
- Hi!

40:58.040 --> 40:59.680
Oh, hey. Cass Wilcott.

40:59.760 --> 41:01.960
- This is David Sandstrom.
- Sandstorm?

41:02.240 --> 41:03.280
Sure thing.

41:03.680 --> 41:05.280
- Oh you're Bob Melnikov.
- Hi!

41:05.560 --> 41:07.920
I loved your talk. So inspiring.

41:08.040 --> 41:09.200
Thanks.

41:10.680 --> 41:13.080
Well, what brings you
to the conference?

41:13.640 --> 41:14.480
Her.

41:15.480 --> 41:17.880
- Hum. Bob.
- I'm her partner.

41:18.200 --> 41:20.560
Oh! So you're working
on the global dimming project together?

41:20.760 --> 41:23.000
Ah! No. It's a common mistake.

41:23.280 --> 41:24.880
Cass is my partner...

41:25.280 --> 41:26.560
Partner.

41:32.240 --> 41:33.040
Oh!

41:33.920 --> 41:36.560
- Oh, Bob, I'll be in touch.
- Okay.

41:36.720 --> 41:38.840
- Nice to meet you.
- You've got my card, right?

41:39.240 --> 41:39.920
Right!

41:41.240 --> 41:42.240
Bye David!

41:42.680 --> 41:43.880
Heather.

41:46.600 --> 41:49.200
I can't believe I didn't notice.
I usually spot that shit right off.

41:49.360 --> 41:50.960
Oh, Bob. Hey, hey.

41:54.800 --> 41:56.680
I get you another drink.

42:05.160 --> 42:06.600
There's not much left to do.

42:06.760 --> 42:08.520
I wish there was, but...

42:08.720 --> 42:10.200
Not in here.

42:10.440 --> 42:12.840
- He can't hear us.
- You don't know that.

42:14.960 --> 42:17.760
It's not easy to see
our loved ones deteriorate, is it?

42:20.320 --> 42:23.440
My sister, his mother, wanted him to live.

42:24.320 --> 42:26.040
I'm all he has.

42:26.480 --> 42:27.920
Should he deteriorate further,

42:28.040 --> 42:30.400
would you like us to take
measures to sustain his life?

42:30.600 --> 42:32.920
Why do you people
keep asking me that?

42:33.120 --> 42:36.080
I'm sorry. It is your decision.

42:37.720 --> 42:38.880
You do understand

42:39.000 --> 42:40.760
that what we're doing
is not helping Glenn,

42:40.880 --> 42:42.720
it's just keeping him alive.

42:45.560 --> 42:47.080
I understand.

42:59.040 --> 43:01.320
I don't know what to do, Glenn.

43:05.160 --> 43:07.080
I'm sorry, Glenn.

43:31.920 --> 43:32.640
What?

43:32.960 --> 43:34.600
- Hey man.
- Owen?

43:34.760 --> 43:36.520
- Yup.
- What's the matter?

43:37.440 --> 43:38.600
She's gone.

43:38.800 --> 43:39.960
What?

43:40.440 --> 43:42.880
I don't know,
she got better and she went home.

43:42.920 --> 43:44.440
What do you mean,
she got better?

43:44.480 --> 43:46.440
What don't you get, man?
She got better.

43:46.600 --> 43:48.400
Why? What did the hospital say?

43:49.800 --> 43:53.160
Who knows?
All I know is that she's gone.

43:54.800 --> 43:57.080
Hmm. That's all, man!

43:57.240 --> 43:58.240
Peace.

